 "logTail": [
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Who are you to me?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The steward. I count what the house holds and what it is owed; you came in under the second column. A man working a thing off gets fair terms from me, and no questions the book does not ask.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"What's the work?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Rice. Half a season's stores, spilled in the kura court where the door gave way in the rains. You rake it in before the rain spoils what's left to count; wage stands as entered — meals.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"What house is this?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The Kurosawa. On the lord's rolls: samurai, one house, standing since before my hand kept the book. In the granary: less than the rolls would suggest, and I will not write the number for a stranger.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Is the work safe?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"A wolf, one, gone bold at the grain store. Grain lost: some. Men lost: none — work by daylight and I intend that count to hold.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "(You say nothing, and take up the rake.)",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"No answer; the rake already moving. Condition: answers with hands — I enter it so, and luck has no column in this book.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Perk unlocked — Hands Before Words: A steady quickness that answers with work — trusting to no luck. (+1 SPD / −1 LUCK)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "You have started to keep count of your own strength — what the day has drawn out of you, and how far that is from Sōan's pallet.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The kura's count is open to you now: rice in, rice out, and the thin line between the store and a lean winter.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The outer court is given to you with the rake: the forecourt, swept ground sized for a household five times this one.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "So you put your hands to it. Rake what grain is still whole back toward the basket, a fistful at a time. We reckon a samurai house’s worth in koku — a year’s eating for one man — and every basket you save us is a measure we need not go begging to the lord to make good.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "You can stop now, when the day is done — set the work down, and let the body take back what it can.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "system",
   "text": "You lie down in the bare corner of the woodshed — no mat yet, the woodpile at your back, the cold coming up through the boards. It is somewhere to stop.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Clear it without my standing over you, and you'll have earned your rice and a dry corner to sleep in. I'll make you no grander promise than that. In this house, none of us holds one.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  }
 ],
